title: Spring Training Group Rides
registration: $5 per day.  Don\'t have to be USA cycling member but need to fill out 1 day license if not member.  Sign up on line or day of event.  Checks pay to RVCC.  Cash or CC accepted.  Registration day of occurs at Brone\'s Bike Shop.  All rides start and finish there.
notes: These are rides which are unsupported.  The target audience is riders who are looking to improve their fitness in a fun and friendly atmosphere.  Most riders have raced or are looking to race in events for the upcoming season.  These are spirited training rides.  More detailed information is provided for each ride the day of each ride.  Show up prepared.  If you can\'t stay in the bunch you\'ll have to find your way back to the shop.
directions:
Address to start and finish of each day is:
Brone\'s Bike Shop
615 S. Main Street
Fountain City, WI  54629

title: Door County Cross of the Century
description:
Event Date:	September 7, 2013
The Door County Cross of the Century cyclocross event is held in conjunction with the Door County Century, a premier, 3,000 participant bike tour in its 35th year. Held entirely at the Door County Fairgrounds in Sturgeon Bay, Wisconsin, this inaugural event will be both a non-competitive warm up for the USAC and WCA cyclocross seasons and will introduce and generate excitement for the sport of cyclocross in northeast Wisconsin. 
As a non-competitive, USAC sanctioned event, this event will not be timed or award participants based on finishing status.  Rather, participants will receive raffle tickets upon completing the allotted race time window and will have the opportunity to win merchandise based on random drawing after each heat.  
This Saturday event will coincide with DC Century Bike Expo and will be run during expo hours, allowing for maximum exposure for racers and spectators. Riding fast and getting dirty is what we are all about!  Mountain bikes and singlespeeds are welcome and encouraged.
course: The unique Cross of the Century course is fast and relatively flat with unique, man-made features.  The 2 mile course will utilize the entire Door County Fairgrounds complex including the 300 long Expo Building, clay stock car track and grandstand, go-cart road course, and pump track style gravel woops.  The course will also feature a quad run-up, two triple barrier sections, a dirt corral and sand pit all within reach of a cold New Belgium Fat Tire and a homemade cup of Booyah!  Lots to rattle your cowbell about! Come and do it in the name of FUN!
registration: Early, online registration is the preferred method for the Cross of the Century.  There are a number of reasons to register in this fashion. Most importantly, by registering online, you receive a wonderful pair of Giro merino wool socks and a great gift from our friends at Stone Creek Coffee when you pick up your race packet! Also, you receive a very nice discount for early registration.  Who doesnt want to save some hard-earned cash? Lastly, it helps us to plan for your arrival and make the necessary operational improvements to maximize your experience in Sturgeon Bay.
directions:
FROM THE SOUTH 
	Take Hwy. 41 or 43 north to Green Bay
	If taking Hwy. 41, take Hwy 43 exit, just after the Velp Ave. exit in Green Bay 
	Take Hwy 43 to Hwy 42/57 north to Sturgeon Bay
	In Sturgeon Bay, and after crossing the large highway bridge, watch for the Michigan St. intersection and turn left. YMCA is at this intersection.
	Continue to 14th Ave. and turn right.  Sturgeon Bay High School is at this intersection.
	Travel .5 miles on 14th and watch for the fairground dirt track grandstand on your right.

	Continue to 14th Ave. and turn right.  Sturgeon Bay High School is at this intersection.

FROM THE NORTH
